- ­¤æż Uses Playwright under the hood, use Playwright MCP for UI tests
- ­¤æż IMPORTANT: Use browser_snapshot before ANY UI work
- ­¤æż Never assume element types/labels without verification
- ­¤æż Workflow: start dev server ŌåÆ browser_navigate ŌåÆ browser_snapshot ŌåÆ verify ŌåÆ interact

## 11. Documentation

### 11.1 JSDoc

- ­¤æż Every exported interface/type must have JSDoc
- ­¤æż File-level JSDoc for config modules
- ­¤æż Use @example where usage isn't obvious
- ­¤æż Use @see <link> to add links to documentation
- ­¤æż Focus on "why" and "how to use", not "what"
- ­¤æż No useless descriptions repeating function name
- ­¤æż Skip JSDoc only if no params AND obvious from name
- ­¤æż Use @deprecated <reason> to mark deprecated code
- ­¤æż All modules must have top level JSDoc with description and usage examples

### 11.2 Code comments

- ­¤æż Avoid obvious comments, only when necessary
- ­¤æż Avoid link to exact lines of code
- ­¤æż Focus on "why" and "how to use", not "what"
- ­¤æż Avoid duplicates comments ŌĆö it means code must be refactored

## 12. Performance

- ­¤æż O(1) lookups: Use Object/Map, not Array.find()
- ­¤æż Avoid map/reduce/for combinations
- ­¤æż Pre-compute lookups, not in render
- ­¤æż Memoize data transformations creating objects/arrays
- ­¤æż Use React.memo with displayName for stable-prop components
- ­¤æż Use factory functions for handlers with parameters
- ­¤æż Profile with React DevTools before adding useMemo/useCallback

## 13. Security

- ­¤æż Validate all external input before processing
- ­¤æż Never trust user data in object operations
- ­¤æż Use crypto.timingSafeEqual() for secret comparison
- ­¤æż Never log or expose secrets, tokens, or PII (logs, error messages, API responses)
- ­¤æż Use exact versions in package.json (no ^ or ~)
- ­¤æż Never enable debug inspector in production
- ­¤æż Never pass untrusted data to Object.assign()
- ­¤æż Use Object.create(null) for user-provided keys
- ­¤æż Use lockfile-based installs in CI/CD (`pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` or `npm ci`)
- ­¤æż Run the matching audit command before deploying (`pnpm audit` or `npm audit`)
- ­¤ż¢ Never use eval() or Function() constructor (`no-eval`)
- ­¤æż Avoid dynamic require()/import() with user-controlled paths
- ­¤æż Use textContent for DOM text insertion, not innerHTML (XSS risk)

## 14. Anti-Patterns

- ­¤ż¢ No CommonJS require() - use ES6 imports
- ­¤æż No callback-based APIs - use Promise-based
- ­¤ż¢ No sync file operations in servers (`n/no-sync`)
- ­¤æż No direct process.exit() - use graceful shutdown
- ­¤æż No CSS Modules/CSS-in-JS - use Tailwind CSS
- ­¤æż No barrel files (index.ts re-exports)
- ­¤æż No unused exports - delete immediately
- ­¤æż No commented-out code - delete it (recover from version control if needed)
- ­¤æż No empty catch blocks - never swallow errors; rethrow or handle with context
- ­¤æż No wrapper functions without added logic
- ­¤æż No Array.find() for lookups - use Map/Object
- ­¤æż No useEffect for state sync
- ­¤æż No inline functions in loops
- ­¤æż No incomplete configurations
- ­¤æż No raw `git commit` ŌĆö use `Skill(autopilot:commits:create)`
- ­¤æż No raw `git checkout -b` / `git branch` ŌĆö use `Skill(autopilot:branch:create)`
- ­¤æż No raw `gh pr create` ŌĆö use `Skill(autopilot:pr:create)`
- ­¤æż No raw `gh issue create` ŌĆö use `Skill(autopilot:issue:create)`

## 16. AI Assistant Workflow

### 16.1 Claude Code

- ­¤æż Use TodoWrite to track complex tasks
- ­¤æż Mark todos as completed immediately
- ­¤æż Parallel tool execution when possible
- ­¤æż Gather context before editing
- ­¤æż Use sub-agents for search-heavy or parallelizable investigation to keep the main context focused
- ­¤æż Use `gh` CLI for GitHub issues, PRs, comments, and Actions info
- ­¤æż **MANDATORY**: Commit only via `Skill(autopilot:commits:create)` ŌĆö no raw `git commit`, no `git commit -m`, no `--amend`, no exceptions. If the autopilot plugin is not installed, follow CONTRIBUTING.md
- ­¤æż **MANDATORY**: Create branches only via `Skill(autopilot:branch:create)` ŌĆö no raw `git checkout -b`, `git branch`, or `git switch -c`. If the autopilot plugin is not installed, follow CONTRIBUTING.md
- ­¤æż **MANDATORY**: Create PRs only via `Skill(autopilot:pr:create)` ŌĆö no raw `gh pr create` or web-UI PR creation. If the autopilot plugin is not installed, follow CONTRIBUTING.md
- ­¤æż **MANDATORY**: Create issues only via `Skill(autopilot:issue:create)` ŌĆö no raw `gh issue create` or web-UI issue creation. If the autopilot plugin is not installed, follow CONTRIBUTING.md

### 16.2 MCP Servers

**context7**, **Ref**, **Exa**: Look up documentation for all technologies

**Playwright**: Verify UI state with browser_snapshot

**Chrome DevTools**: Performance analysis, network debugging, console logging, etc.

## 17. Code Review

- All rules from CLAUDE.md must be applied to the code review
