- [Stack rule sets](./rules/) ŌĆö `Bun`, `Bun+React+Tailwind`, `NodeJS+React`, `NodeJS+React+Tailwind`

## GitHub Actions

- [`files-sync`](./.github/actions/files-sync/README.md) ŌĆö sync declared files from upstream repos and open one PR with the differences
- [`upstream-sync`](./.github/actions/upstream-sync/README.md) ŌĆö aggregate the five upstream maintenance syncs behind one action; every kind on by default, opt out per kind
- [`agents-rules-sync`](./.github/actions/agents-rules-sync/README.md) ŌĆö sync the stack-appropriate `rules/<stack>.md` into `CLAUDE.md` based on `package.json` `agents.rules`
- [`contributing-check`](./.github/actions/contributing-check/README.md) ŌĆö validate branch name, commit messages, and PR title against `CONTRIBUTING.md`
- [`contributing-sync`](./.github/actions/contributing-sync/README.md) ŌĆö sync `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`, `LICENSE.md`, and the contributing workflow from upstream
- [`licenses-audit`](./.github/actions/licenses-audit/README.md) ŌĆö regenerate the license report on dependency-changing PRs, auto-commit drift on same-repo PRs, and fail fork PRs that ship stale license data
- [`release-action`](./.github/actions/release-action/README.md) ŌĆö conventional-commit-driven release pipeline for npm packages, GitHub Actions, and Claude plugins
- [`release-automerge`](./.github/actions/release-automerge/README.md) ŌĆö merge an approved, all-green release PR (`^release-`), driven by an event-based workflow so `release-publish.yml` runs without a manual click
- [`code-review-action`](./.github/actions/code-review-action/README.md) ŌĆö AI code review for pull requests via Claude Code, with a react mode for replying to bot mentions
- [`auto-label`](./.github/actions/auto-label/README.md) ŌĆö label PRs with `<scope>/<workspace-member>` labels for the workspace members a diff touches, and prune orphan labels on merge
- [`repomix-sync`](./.github/actions/repomix-sync/README.md) ŌĆö sync the `repomix-pack` workflow and `repomix.config.json` from upstream so each consumer commits its own codebase snapshot
- [`release-sync`](./.github/actions/release-sync/README.md) ŌĆö sync the release pipeline workflows (`release`, `publish`, `release-automerge`) from upstream so each consumer runs the same release flow

